 "overview": "\u003Cp\u003EOPEL Technologies is the developer of the planar optoelectronic technology (POET) semiconductor process, which fuses electronic and optical devices on a single chip, using a proprietary monolithic fabrication process.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003EAlready demonstrated in numerous devices, including sensors, thyristors, lasers and modulators - and used as the platform for ongoing development of military and aerospace applications, including infrared sensor arrays and ultra-low-power random access memory for NASA and other agencies - POET has the potential to propel the semiconductor industry into the next of iteration of Moore\u0026#8217;s Law.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003EWith 36 patents issued and 6 patents pending for its POET process, OPEL\u0026#8217;s proprietary POET platform enables high-speed and power-efficient applications for numerous commercial verticals including servers, tablet computers and smartphones. \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003EOPEL\u0026#8217;s common shares trade on the TSX Venture Exchange under the symbol \u0026#8220;OPL\u0026#8221;.\u003C/p\u003E",
